reviews.text:
MOST OVER-PRICED ramen in HK. Soup is fair, pork is fair, noodle is fair: nothing is impressive. Regret that I spent $272 on 2 bowls of not-so-good ramen. 

Do NOT recommend.
It was good. Nothing to call home about. I had the miso based ramen. Broth was tasty but the noodles were off.

Nice environment and service. Love the styling and atmosphere developed and the professional chefs. Food is quite ordinary though. Not gonna be something I expect at like couple hundred bucks with Michelin rating. I won't say it's overpriced owing to such context but it's like... you know, it could be better.

must try duck soup noodle (Ajitama Kamo Paitan Soba). a small workshop on the left can see fresh noodle making. You should not miss it! great location reflects on the price but I will definitely back.
This restaurant does not deserve the Michelin star one bit! The worst ramen I’ve ever had in hk. The char siu tasted like boiled meat in salty water. Butao next door is cheaper and of better quality.

reviews.text:
豫園 (銅鑼灣)
銅鑼灣登龍街18號 V Point 26樓

招牌松子鮮魚最開胃，可以加碗白飯送汁!

今天本來是去吃火鍋的，不過朋友病了轉了中餐。朋友本來電話去訂位說沒有位不能預訂，但之後我們walk in就有位。這家餐廳是全層分左面廳，右面廳。左面廳全部沒有景，右面廳裝修非常華麗。如果真的要去吃就要訂有景的一邊。

食物方面，我覚得整體ok, 我特別喜歡招牌松子魚，酸酸甜甜一整條，好味。脆皮素鴨也很出色。

如果想食高力豆沙或豆沙鍋餅就要預早叫定好樣廚房準備。那天我們大約10:30pm叫這兩款甜品，全都沒有！
One of the new high rise building consisting of upmarket restaurants.
餐飲為主，但宣傳唔多，下面又冇餐牌可以睇
貴價又難食的高檔菜式

I had only one drink there, so I can't say much about the food but the view is pretty good and the staff was super friendly. They even made some discount on the occasion of my b-day and offered some shots. I thinks its definitely worth trying, at least, once)

result.name: Tsuta Japanese Soba Noodles

reviews.text: This is a ramen shop that thinks it’s different because it uses thin noodles. No buckwheat or somen in sight.
Good ramen with light soup.

There are a lot of Ramen restaurants located at Tang Lung Street and this is one of the very good one. The soup base is delicious and the noodles are equally good. However the BBQ pork is not as good as some of the nearby shop.

Is a famous Japanese ramen, not the classic but a creative one. Black truffle source is added to most of its ramen, nice creative touch.  US19 for a bowl of ramen is certainly the top of the game.  There are a few not so famous but including 1 or 2 are from established JAPANESE ramen chain which serve more classic style in lower price.
Shorter queue compare to other ramen places. Quality is good but a bit pricy.

reviews.text:
因為男朋友很喜歡吃拉麵，所以便推介了我一同前往這間喻為米芝蓮級數的拉麵店吃一頓。

這次已經是我第二次來吃，因為很喜歡餐廳的照燒雞拉麵。

照燒雞拉麵有的材料也在餐牌上寫得一清二楚，我這款照燒雞拉麵則是有兩片雞肉、生菜、洋蔥粒、粟米和拉麵以及雞湯。

拉麵湯有非常濃郁好喝的雞油鮮味，很滑口，而且不覺得油膩。雞肉用真空煮至半熟，再用熱湯蓋過雞肉至剛好全熟，所以非常嫩滑。配菜跟整個拉麵非常搭，一絕。

拉麵店可以維持水準一流，非常推介。

我去了吃了一次最便宜的也要159元，湯又沒有味道，D面真是很難食！
      我感到很失望(我懷疑去測量的人員被收賣)
垃圾 湯冇味 拉面質素差 間店推介既154蚊既醬油拉面同市面上3蚊既出前XX冇咩大分別 叉燒冇調味過 簡單啲黎講冇味 我畀負5分 即係貼錢我先會再食過 仲要貼90蚊以上先考慮
